arts.ttl: Parma wins at last for new coach Cuesta as Lazio put three past struggling Genoa
arts.sum: Torino had all 11 men in and around the six-yard box but Pellegrino rose highest to head home a corner kick and lift Parma into 14th place. Cyril Ngonge equalized for Torino three minutes later when he created space for himself on the edge of the box then unleashed a lovely 20-meter drive into the far corner.

arts.ttl: Genoa vs Lazio wraps up the fifth matchday
arts.sum: Lazio have gone without goals for two consecutive away matches in Serie A - this had not happened since the 2020/21 season when they failed to score for 3 matches in a row, away to Fiorentina, Roma, and Sassuolo, all in May. Genoa aim to achieve their first win of the season, while Lazio hope to get back on track after their derby defeat.
